entries.femaleVariant: You've got the data – what now?
What were you working on at Cytech?
You got your program. What now?
What exactly were you working on behind the corp's back?
Well, I can't afford to set up my own lab – even if it was in my own pad. I'll have to someone who'll be interested in what I've got.
Careful with Cytech. The sooner you're off their radar – the better.
Don't worry. I've got a fixer on that already.
They'll find someone who can encrypt their eddy trail and screen me from Cytech's investigation.
Did you know that Cytech codes its drivers to get users addicted to only certain brands of implant? Of course you didn't know.
You chip an implant from the competition – your body reacts like your hand's been cut off, or you removed a kidney.
I tried to script a program that would find and delete this kind of algorithm from every kind of implant.
Wow, respect. I'll keep my fingers crossed.
Couple that with artificial withdrawal symptoms and you've got a whole army of users who can't live without your product.
